# Crontab Example

For automatic daily backups, add this to your crontab:

```bash
# Edit crontab
crontab -e

# Add this line (runs at 03:00 UTC daily):
0 3 * * * /root/openclaw-stock-home/.openclaw/workspace/repositories/openclaw-backup-utils/backup.sh --cron --upload-google-drive
```

## Schedule Options

| Schedule | Cron Expression | Description |
|----------|-----------------|-------------|
| Daily at 3 AM | `0 3 * * *` | Daily backup |
| Every 6 hours | `0 */6 * * *` | 4x daily backup |
| Weekly (Sunday 4 AM) | `0 4 * * 0` | Weekly backup |
| Monthly (1st, 5 AM) | `0 5 1 * *` | Monthly backup |

## Google Drive Upload

To enable Google Drive uploads, ensure:
1. `gog-agentic` MCP server is configured
2. `backup-rules.json` has `parentId` set (or use default `1b9uskrej-gjGVG-RmeaSYdPk0deUOa3R`)

## Monitoring

To monitor backups, check:
```bash
# View backup log
tail -f /root/openclaw-stock-home/.openclaw/backups/backup.log

# List backups
ls -lh /root/openclaw-stock-home/.openclaw/backups/
```

## Dry Run (No Upload)

For testing without upload:
```bash
0 3 * * * /root/openclaw-stock-home/.openclaw/workspace/repositories/openclaw-backup-utils/backup.sh --cron
```

## Manual Test

To test cron job manually:
```bash
/root/openclaw-stock-home/.openclaw/workspace/repositories/openclaw-backup-utils/backup.sh --cron --upload-google-drive
```

## Cron Logs

System cron logs are at:
```bash
# Debian/Ubuntu
tail -f /var/log/syslog | grep CRON
```
